==English==
===Etymology===
Latin ''[[refutare]]''

===Pronunciation===
American ([[SAMPA]]): [r@"fjut]

===Transitive verb===
'''to refute''' (''[[present participle]]'' '''refuting''', ''[[past tense]] and [[past participle]]'' '''refuted''')

#To [[prove]] (something) to be [[false]] or [[incorrect]].
#(''Erroneous'') To [[deny]] the [[truth]] or [[correctness]] of (something).

====Usage note====
*  To refute a proposition is to show beyond argument that it is false.  
The erroneous use of "refute" to mean "to deny" is contrary to the essence of the word, and best avoided by those who value precision in language.

